# OpenFinance AI — Platform Requirements

## Vision
AI-powered personal finance automation platform: "Zapier + AI + Banking Automation"
Users link bank accounts (simulated), aggregate financial data, run AI agents, automate decisions.

## Tech Stack
- Backend: Python FastAPI, SQLite (SQLAlchemy), pytest
- AI: Real LLM agents (OpenAI default, Anthropic, Bedrock future-ready)
- Config: LLM_PROVIDER, OPENAI_API_KEY, LLM_MODEL env vars

## Architecture Invariants
- LLM produces structured JSON; never mutates DB directly
- LLM can only call approved platform tools (no arbitrary code)
- All agent runs logged with: prompt, reasoning, data used, actions, errors
- Payment actions require approval unless explicitly allowed
- All actions stored as audit logs

## Core Models
User, BankAccount, Transaction, EmailConnection, EmailMessage,
AgentDefinition, AgentRun, PaymentInstruction, AccountTransferInstruction,
DirectDebitInstruction, Subscription, AuditLog

## Agent Flow
1. Build financial context → 2. LLM prompt → 3. Structured plan (JSON)
→ 4. Policy validation → 5. Tool execution → 6. Store AgentRun

## Built-in Agents (LLM-powered)
Affordability AI, Spending Behavior AI, Subscription Tracker AI,
Payday Monitor, Manage Finance Agent, Invoice Executor

## Custom Agents
Users define: name, goal, trigger, data sources, actions, execution mode,
spending limits. LLM interprets intent → safe structured plan → approved tools only.

## Key APIs
- User insights: summary, transactions, insights, subscriptions
- Agent management: list, enable, disable, run, view runs
- Payments: payments, transfers, direct-debits (simulated)
- Simulator: POST /simulator/transactions
- Email: connect, list emails
